ratings.rComments: His lectures are kinda boring and he speaks with a monotone voice. He knows his stuff, but the delivery is not so good. He wrote the textbook so everything can be found in there. The modeling assignments are pretty easy, the sketching assignments are not hard, but time consuming. Start the group project early!!!!

This class is extremely tedious and time consuming. It's only offered for 3 credit hours which is far less than what it should be. The TAs can be pretty helpful but Leake's lectures are extremely long and boring. It's hard not to fall asleep unless you're very interested in the subject. Be prepared to do a lot of tedious work.
Guys, start the design project early if you're in CEE.  As far as Leake, he knows his stuff, but the delivery is pretty boring and he isn't nearly as involved as he should be.

If you can get past the boring delivery, he actually explains the material pretty well.  Start the design project early.  On the last week, I spent 4-5 hours a few days in a row fixing parts and working on the assembly.  Exams are relatively easy, but you do have to know the material well enough to be able to work quickly

You're most likely taking this class a requirement and there's no avoiding Leake. Therefore just accept the facts of the class: There are frequent sketching assignments that are graded hard but if you put in effort they are fine. Then the tests are taken directly from his book so if you study it exactly the few nights before you should be fine.

If you have to take the class, make sure you pay attention to your assignments posted on Compass. The design project will take up a huge chunk of your time, so make sure you know what you need to do ahead of time. Lectures are boring, hopefully you get a good TA as they end up being the people who grade everything and can help you on modeling.

He has repeatedly cancelled assignments, then at the last minute required it again. We were tested on material we were not taught nor told we had to know it. Points were taken off assignments if we didn't write our name in all caps. When our TA was asked if the information was even useful, he said no. Also we had to the useless textbook he wrote.

This class is not really helpful. I am not going to lie, I did enjoy learning how to use Autodesk Inventor but the sketching stuff was pointless. Not only did they hurt my grade but I never need to use it in my life. This class was not worth all the hours i put in. Also the prof. is really boring. His lectures are pointless and his tests are hard.
Most boring lectures ever. But, if you take notes it will help out in the long run. Also, read the texts.
he sucks at teaching! and he hates his students! extremely boring lecture and tons of assignments dues every week and he never teach.

Easily the most ineffective professor I've had at UIUC. His lectures provide no insight into the material, or the slightest notion of enthusiasm. The majority of this class is taught by the TAs who struggle to keep up with his disorganized scheduling and thought processes. Do yourself a big favor and start the design project ASAP.

Leake is a sad man.  He hates his job and he hates teaching, that much is obvious.  #1 problem with the class is lack of organization and scheduling.  Due dates are revealed a few days before the date (even on major assignments), directions are cryptic and sometimes irrelevant.  Just get your project moded ASAP because it WILL be due unexpectedly!!
Boring lecture, no denying that. Interesting course material. Good ONLY if you like spatial visualization.
He didn't keep anyone interested in the material. He was very boring. The written exams definitely weren't easy either. A lot of work required for the class as well.
This class is extremely boring. I am a CEE major and this class has nothing to do with my major. This is completely useless. Not to mention his monotone, dull and boring voice.

I had his lecture at 10 and still fell asleep in class. I had to go since he took attendance. Exams are heavily dependent on the tedious textbook he wrote. I still remember how the book said an advantage of using a mechanical pencil is the fact that you don't have to sharpen it. Also, it advised to use an eraser that won't smudge. Still, an easy A.

More than half of the students in lecture are either not paying attention or sleeping, but he has no one to blame but himself. He is lazy, boring, and doesn't seem to care about the students understanding of the material. It is not a terribly hard class, but it's certainly not an enjoyable one.

Very,very boring. This class is hard if you do not have good visualization skills. Lectures are pointless to go to. Get started early on the design project even tho I know you won't. For the written tests,read directly out of the book because he wrote it.
He's a very cute old man! But he is reallly boring. He knows his stuff though!
Very helpful. His lectures...I'll be honest... Makes me sleepy. But if u manage to stay awake. Every lil point he say is helpful.
He is not as bad as many ppl said to me. Always willing to help. Hws, however, can be a real pain. In general, this class will cost you a decent chunk of time.

His lectures can be boring, but the modeling labs were actually pretty fun.  TIp of advice: Start the design project ASAP. Spent WAY too much time on that project for a 3 hr class. Its most of the grade since there's no final. What may seem like irrelevant info in lectures may end up showing up on exams. This class wasn't too bad and Leake is OK.

Not very relevant for CEE majors, though currently a requirement. A lot of hours a week required for only 3 credit hours. Boring lectures, but attendance is always taken. His book is practically his powerpoints, so you don't get many other views on subject matter. Should really be more than 3 credit hours.

Horrible exams.  Irrelevent assignments.  Boring lectures.  The final project was the biggest waste of time I've ever done.  I learned more about drawing on CADD in one week as an intern than in this whole class.

Pretty easy class. The modeling assignments aren't that bad, and sketching really isn't bad either. Just make sure to study the sketching theory before the written exams. As for the design project -- START EARLY. If you don't, you'll spend entire nights rendering images in the lab, which isn't fun -- trust me, I've done it.
He might be boring but you can tell he really knows his stuff. He is getting old but the class is still alright.
Cool guy. not too exciting early on but a good class.
He is just a jerk.
Sure, some of the class material, such as inventor assignments are fun. But, it seems Leake tries his hardest to make the class as boring as possible.

He can be very boring in lectures, but he's a nice guy willing to help. Inventor assignments are interesting and exams fair in content. Written exams test vocabulary and theory and can be tricky, but if you read the book and the lectures notes beforehand you won't have any problems.

He is a super nice person and knows his stuff! Even though it is a little boring in his lecture, if you are truly passionate about engineering you will be able to pay attention. I personally loved the class with all the work it required!
VERY boring lecture.  Tough class which requires a lot of work.

The class really isn't that hard if you play around with the programs enough.  Lecture is extremely boring.  Tests ask a lot of vocab and things that don't really matter but if you go over the lecture slides beforehand, you should do alright.  Be prepared to learn a lot on your own outside of class.

incredibly boring. he didn't seem very intelligent- i cannot fathom how he wrote a book on Inventor...he also assigned projects that weren't meant to be designed on Inventor (e.g. an entire airport). additionally, he made the assumption that everyone had taken a CAD class in high school, and completely left 1/3 of the class in the dust

Very dry. Hard to stay attentive during lectures, where he does take attendance. He doesn't communicate with his TAs, so it's difficult to know what to expect. On our first test he told us the day of, "we haven't gone over this at all, but there will be questions on it."
Easy, easy class if you are good at 3D visualization and modeling. Lecture is not entirely helpful. Professor is okay; neither fun nor bad.
Monotonous voice, pointless class, completely unhelpful, finds his class to be far superior than others
This guy is the definitioin of boring.  Accomplishes little in class and the test are irrelevant.  He needs to to revise the course.  Probably hasnt done that since the 90s.
Very monotone
this guy is a moron.  go get a life and stop playing with autodesk inventor for fun.
Pretend this class is for 5 credit hrs bc it should be. The final project takes so much work, dont get behind but the CAD stuff is cool
boring lectures that he took attendance for.  A lot of vocab and true false on the tests.  Very picky

he is very boring to listen to, if you go to lecture you might as well stay in bed. read the designated book areas before the test and you will be fine. dont forget about the online lecture quizzes. bring inventor book to computer lab.
Too much work for credit given.  Sounds like a robot
Most monotonous boring guy in the world!!
He puts EVERYONE to sleep
Zzzzzzzzzzzzzzz
Puts people to sleep during the lectures, but seemed interested in the projects that were due at the end of the year
No Comments
Explains things quite well, but has an easy time putting people to sleep.
Voice is monotone but he knows what he is talking about, seems eager to help students.
